## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="9a710-118">次の例では、ハンドラーを`SpeechRecognized`のイベントを<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>または<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer>オブジェクト、および関連付けられているに関する情報の一部<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-118">The following example shows a handler for the `SpeechRecognized` event of a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> object, and some of the information about the associated <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Handle the SpeechRecognized event.   
void SpeechRecognizedHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
  
  // The following code illustrates some of the information available  
  // in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("Grammar({0}), {1}: {2}",  
    e.Result.Grammar.Name, e.Result.Audio.Duration, e.Result.Text);  
  
  // Display the semantic values in the recognition result.  
  foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in e.Result.Semantics)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine(" {0} key: {1}",  
      child.Key, child.Value.Value ?? "null");  
  }  
  Console.WriteLine();  
  
  // Display information about the words in the recognition result.  
  foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
  {  
    RecognizedAudio audio = e.Result.GetAudioForWordRange(word, word);  
    Console.WriteLine(" {0,-10} {1,-10} {2,-10} {3} ({4})",  
      word.Text, word.LexicalForm, word.Pronunciation,  
      audio.Duration, word.DisplayAttributes);  
  }  
  
  // Display the recognition alternates for the result.  
  foreach (RecognizedPhrase phrase in e.Result.Alternates)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine(" alt({0}) {1}", phrase.Confidence, phrase.Text);  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="9a710-121">認識<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>はの値によって並べ替えられます、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>プロパティ。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-121">Recognition <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> are ordered by the values of their <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> properties.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9a710-122">特定のフレーズの信頼度の値では、語句が、入力と一致する確率を示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-122">The confidence value of a given phrase indicates the probability that the phrase matches the input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9a710-123">最上位の信頼度の値を持つ語句は、ほとんどの場合、入力に一致する語句です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-123">The phrase with the highest confidence value is the phrase that most likely matches the input.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9a710-124">各<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>個別にし、その他の信頼度の値を指定せずに値を評価する必要があります<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-124">Each <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> value should be evaluated individually and without reference to the confidence values of other <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9a710-125">プロパティを<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>継承<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>信頼度スコアが最も高い語句に関する詳細情報を提供します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-125">The properties that the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> inherits from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> provide detailed information about the phrase with the highest confidence score.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9a710-126">用途の 1 つ、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>コレクションは、自動化されたエラーの修正。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-126">One use for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> collection is for automated error correction.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9a710-127">たとえば、ディレクトリのダイアログを設計するときに、アプリケーションでした入力をユーザーにされている場合、アプリケーションから認識イベントでは、正しい情報として、「おっしゃいました 'Anna' ですか?」を確認するにはかどうか、ユーザーが話す"no"し、アプリケーションが十分に高のある任意の代替のユーザーをクエリでした<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>スコア。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-127">For example, when designing a directory dialog, an application could prompt the user to check if the application has the correct information from a recognition event, as in, "Did you say 'Anna'?" If the user says "no", then the application could query the user about any alternates that had a high enough <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> score.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9a710-128">音声認識と代替認識の使用の詳細については、次を参照してください。[音声認識](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361633(v=office.14))と[音声認識イベントを使用した](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482)します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9a710-128">For more information about speech recognition and the use of recognition alternates, see [Speech Recognition](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361633(v=office.14)) and [Using Speech Recognition Events](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span></span>  
  
   
  
